{META_DATA}: Usual Suspects
{META_DATA}: Written By Christopher McQuarrie
{META_DATA}: Produced and Directed By Bryan Singer
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Revised, 05/25/94 White Revised, 06/01/94 Blue Revised, 06/07/94 Pink Revised, 06/11/94 Yellow
{META_DATA}: SCRIPT DATE 5/25/94
{META_DATA}: 1 -BLACK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lonely sound of a buoy bell in the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Water slapping against a smooth, flat surface in rhythm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The creaking of wood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Off in the very far distance, one can make out the sound of sirens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY, a single match ignites and invades the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It quivers for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dimly lit hand brings the rest of the pack to the match.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A plume of yellow-white flame flares and illuminates the battered face of DEAN KEATON, age forty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His salty-gray hair is wet and matted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face drips with water or sweat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A large cut runs the length of his face from the corner of his eye to his chin.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It bleeds freely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An un-lit cigarette hangs in the corner of his mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the half-light we can make out that he is on the deck of a large boat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A yacht, perhaps, or a small freighter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sits with his back against the front bulkhead of the wheel house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His legs are twisted at odd, almost impossible angles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A thin trail of liquid runs past his feet and off into the darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton lights the cigarette on the burning pack of matches before throwing them into the liquid.
{META_DATA}: The liquid IGNITES with a poof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flame runs up the stream, gaining in speed and intensity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It begins to ripple and rumble as it runs down the deck towards the stern.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 2 EXT. BOAT - NIGHT - STERN 2'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A stack of oil drums rests on the stern.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are stacked on a palette with ropes at each corner that attach it to a huge crane on the dock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the barrels has been punctured at it's base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gasoline trickles freely from the hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flame is racing now towards the barrels.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton smiles weakly to himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flame is within a few yards of the barrels when another stream of liquid splashes onto the gas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flame fizzles out pitifully with a hiss.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two feet straddle the flame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A stream of urine flows onto the deck from between them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLUE 06/01/94
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 2.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of a fly zipping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Follow the feet as they move over to where Keaton rests at the wheel house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANE UP to the waist of the unknown man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a pack of cigarettes out of one pocket and a strange antique lighter from the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is gold, with a clasp that folds down over the flint.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man flicks up the clasp with his thumb and strikes it with his index finger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a fluid motion,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: somewhat showy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton looks up at the man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A look of realization crosses his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is followed by frustration, anger, and finally resignation.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: How are you, Keaton?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KEATON
{DIALOGUE}: I'd have to say my spine was broken, Keyser.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spits the name out like it was poison.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man puts the lighter back in his pocket and reaches under his jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He produces a stainless .38 revolver.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Ready?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KEATON
{DIALOGUE}: What time is it?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand with the gun turns over, turning the gold watch on its wrist upward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of sirens is closer now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Headed this way.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Twelve thirty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton grimaces bitterly and nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns his head away and takes another drag.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand with the gun waits long enough for Keaton to enjoy his last drag before pulling the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GUNSHOT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of Keaton's body slumping onto the deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: YELLOW 06/11/94
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 3.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE OUT ACROSS THE DECK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Below is the stream of gasoline still flowing freely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of the gasoline igniting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The flame runs in front of us towards the barrels, finally leaping up in a circle around the drums, burning the wood of the pallet and licking the spouting stream as it pours from the hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE OUT ACROSS THE DOCK, away from the boat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pier to which the boat is moored is littered with DEAD BODIES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Twenty or more men have been shot to pieces and lie scattered everywhere in what can only be the aftermath of a fierce fire-fight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A BARGE COMES INTO VIEW.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the deck of the barge is a tangle of cables and girders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mesh of steel and rubber leaves a dark and open cocoon beneath its base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE INTO THE DARKNESS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sirens are close now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Almost here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of fire raging out of control.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SIRENS BLARING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIRES SQUEALING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CAR DOORS OPENING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FEET POUNDING THE PAVEMENT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE FURTHER, SLOWER, INTO THE DARKNESS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Voices yelling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: New light flickering in the surrounding darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY, AN EXPLOSION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TOTAL BLACKNESS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the voice of ROGER &quot;VERBAL&quot; KINT, whom we will soon meet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VERBAL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: New York.
{DIALOGUE}: - six weeks ago.
{DIALOGUE}: A truck loaded with stripped gun parts got jacked outside of Queens.
{DIALOGUE}: The driver didn't see anybody, but somebody fucked up.
{DIALOGUE}: He heard a voice.
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes, that's all you need.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YELLOW 06/11/94
{DIALOGUE}: 4.
{DIALOGUE}: BOOM
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 3 INT. DARK APARTMENT - DAY - NEW YORK - SIX WEEKS PRIOR TO PRESENT DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The black explodes with the opening of a door into a dark room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Outside, the hall is filled with blinding white light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shadows in the shapes of men flood into the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We can make out men in hoods with flashlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are laden with weapons.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICES
{DIALOGUE}: POLICE.
{DIALOGUE}: SEARCH WARRANT.
{DIALOGUE}: DON'T MOVE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a blur of violent action and sound.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 'Beams of flashlights cut the darkness in all directions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FINALLY:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dozen flashlights land on one man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lies naked in bed, Merging from a deep sleep.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He squints at the flood of blinding white light, more annoyed than frightened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He nearly laughs at the sound of countless guns cocking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is McMANUS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Age twenty-eight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Mr. McManus?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: McMANUS Yeah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VOICE (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: Police.
{DIALOGUE}: We have a warrant for your arrest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: McMANUS Will they be serving coffee downtown?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two dozen black gloved hands grab him and yank him out of bed.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 4 INT. AUTO BODY SHOP - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An old paint mixer vibrates furiously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TODD HOCKNEY, a dark, portly man in his thirties is working on an old Fire-bird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A YOUNG HISPANIC KID mixes paint a few feet away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY, the garage door opens TO REVEAL:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: YELLOW 06/11/94 4A .
{DIALOGUE}: A row of five men silhouetted by the bright sun.
{DIALOGUE}: Hockney squints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: YELLOW 06/11/94
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 5.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HOCKNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Can I help you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hockney's voice is gruff.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN
{DIALOGUE}: Todd Hockney'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hockney reaches for something just inside the door of the Fire-bird.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HOCKNEY
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All six men INSTANTLY PRODUCE GUNS and aim them at Hockney.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MAN
{DIALOGUE}: Police.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hockney withdraws a filthy towel and wipes grease and sweat from his forehead.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HOCKNEY
{DIALOGUE}: We don't do gun repair.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: S EXT. STREET - NEW YORK - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FRED FENSTER, a tall, thin man in his thirties strolls casually down the street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is dressed conspicuously in a loud suit and tie with shoes that have no hope of matching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smokes a cigarette and chews gum at the same time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He happens to glance over his shoulder and notice a brown Ford sedan with four men in it cruising along the curb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He picks up his step a little.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ford keeps up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks ahead at the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries to look as comfortable as he can, checking his watch as though remembering an appointment he is late for.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Ford stays right on him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY, he bolts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets no more than a few yards before cars pour out of every conceivable nook and cranny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Brakes are squealing, radios squawking, guns cocking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fenster is surrounded instantly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops short and flaps his hands on his thighs in defeat.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 6 INT. MONDINO'S RESTAURANT - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An attractive man and woman walk quickly through the front of a small New York cafe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are charged with nervous, excited energy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: YELLOW 06/11/94
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 5A.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man is DEAN KEATON, a well dressed, sturdy looking man in his forties with slightly graying hair.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks much better than he did in the opening scene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The woman with him is EDIE FINNERAN, age thirty-three, poised and attractive - Easily the calmer of the two.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLUE 06/01/94
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 6.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come to a staircase at the back of the restaurant leading down to a dark room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Edie takes Keaton's arm and stops him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDIE
{DIALOGUE}: Let me look at you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton is uncomfortable in his suit, or perhaps the situation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still, he smiles with genuine warmth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Edie straightens his tie and picks microscopic imperfections from his lapel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDIE (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Now remember, this is another kind of business.
{DIALOGUE}: They don't earn your respect.
{DIALOGUE}: You owe it to them.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't stare them down but don't look away either.
{DIALOGUE}: Confidence.
{DIALOGUE}: They are fools not to trust you.
{DIALOGUE}: That's the attitude.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KEATON
{DIALOGUE}: I'm having a stroke.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDIE
{DIALOGUE}: You've come far.
{DIALOGUE}: You're a good man.
{DIALOGUE}: I love you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton blinks then stammers, looking for a response.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAUSE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: EDIE (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Live with it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She kisses him and runs down the steps with Keaton close behind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton playfully grabs her ass and she nearly stumbles down the stairs.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 7 INT. RESTAURANT - DOWNSTAIRS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come to the bottom of the steps giggling and jabbing each other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Once off the stairs they instantly transform as though hit with cold air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They assume a cool, professional exterior and walk two feet apart.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One would look at them and see only two business associates here to ply their trade.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk across the dimly lit dining room to a table in the far corner where two men are already waiting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The first is MR. FORTIER, age thirty-five, the other is MR. RENAULT, age
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sixty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Both men are impeccably dressed with a distinguished air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stand and smile.
