{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 11 INT. LOCK-UP HALLWAY - NIGHT 11'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A police officer steps into the frame and opens the steel door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: FOLLOW A PAIR OF FEET as they shuffle across the cement floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shoes are shabby and worn, as are the wrinkled pants that hang too low and loose at the cuffs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The right foot is turned slightly inward and falls with a hard limp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is clear that the knee does not extend fully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound of a steel door opening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bottom corner of a steel cage comes into view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another set of feet falls into step with the first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another steel door and another set of feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another door, another and another.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Five pairs of feet walk single file down the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The lame feet are in the front of the line.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come to another steel door, this one solid and covered with dents and rivets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CRANE UP TO REVEAL:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ROGER KINT, VERBAL to his few friends.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has a deeply lined face, making his thirty-odd years a good guess at best.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From his twisted left hand, we can see that he suffers from a slight but not debilitating palsy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him are Dean Keaton, Fred Fenster, McManus and Todd Hockney.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: t
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal steps through the door, followed by the rest.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: VERBAL (V.O.)
