{CHARACTER_NAME}: VERBAL (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: They drilled us all night.
{DIALOGUE}: Somebody was pissed about that truck getting knocked off and the cops had nothing.
{DIALOGUE}: They were hoping somebody would slip.
{DIALOGUE}: Give them something to go on.
{DIALOGUE}: They knew we wouldn't fight it because they knew how to lean on us.
{DIALOGUE}: They'd been doing it forever.
