{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 19 EXT. PIER - DAY - SAN PEDRO - PRESENT DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is morning in the aftermath of the opening scene.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harsh sunlight shines on a line of body bags on the dock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Police swarm everywhere, photographers are taking pictures of the scene while a team of men in rolled up sleeves and plastic gloves pick at the remains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two men on a fire boat operate a water cannon, dousing the smoldering remains of a burned-out ships hull.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Watching this from the edge of the pier is a man in a dark suit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is SPECIAL AGENT JACK BAER of the F.B.I.
