{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: McManus picks it up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He trains a pistol on each bodyguard and takes a breath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are some ten feet apart and moving erratically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hockney and Fenster constantly fall in the line of fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: McManus walks around the four men, keeping a pistol trained on each of the guards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally he comes to an angle where they are all in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One guard is a few feet away, the other is ten feet past him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: McMANUS' P.O.V.
