{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 140 EXT. BARGE - NIGHT - ONE WEEK PRIOR 140'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal is hiding in the tangle of girders and cables on the barge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: VERBAL'S P.O.V.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keaton's body is completely obscured.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man in a suit strides across the deck over to Keaton, stopping to relieve himself on a small fire on the deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He walks up and stands over Keaton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two men exchange words and the man in the suit pulls out a pistol.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He points it at Keaton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: RED AND BLUE LIGHTS FLASH BEHIND VERBAL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can just make out police cars coming in the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BANG
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal hears a shot from the deck of the boat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns in time to see the man in the suit running across the deck toward the gangway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal can barely see the man from where he is now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man in the suit is covered by shadows and the poor angle from the barge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal strains to see but he cannot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man in the suit stops long enough to pull out a lighter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and walks back across the deck and out of sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later flames leap up from on the deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mesh of steel and rubber leaves a dark and open cocoon at its base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MOVE INTO THE DARKNESS.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sirens are close now.
