{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 158 INT. DISPATCHER'S OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jack Beer pulls the sheet out of the fax machine and turns it over, revealing the composite sketch of Keyser SOZE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Though crude and distorted, one cannot help but notice how much it leaks like VERBAL KINT.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 159 EXT. STREET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The driver gets out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT IS KOBAYASHI, or the man we have come to know as such.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles to Verbal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Verbal steps off of the curb, returning the smile as he opens the passenger door and gets in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The man called Kobayashi gets in the driver's seat and pulls away .
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment later, Agent David Kujan of U.S. Customs wanders into the frame, looking around much in the way a child would when lost at the circus.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes no notice of the car pulling out into traffic, blending in with the rest of the cars filled with people on their way back to work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLACK
